# AnimOrg Backend Stabilization Implementation Plan

This plan outlines the diagnosis and fixing of the stability issues in the AnimOrg backend.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> - We will run the backend locally using `npm run dev` and perform verification using standard `curl` or automated testing script requests.
> - No new endpoints or architectural changes are planned.
> - We will replace Jikan API concurrent storm (`Promise.all`) inside [HomeService](file:///m:/NEXORA%20GEN/AnimOrg2/backend/src/services/HomeService.ts#6-43) with sequential or controlled parallelization (`Promise.allSettled`), and improve retry-backoff algorithms.

## Proposed Changes

---

### Http & Retry Layer (axiosClient)

#### [MODIFY] [axiosClient.ts](file:///m:/NEXORA%20GEN/AnimOrg2/backend/src/utils/axiosClient.ts)
- Temporarily replace with a minimal axios instance to isolate issues (Step 1).
- Improve retry policy:
  - Do not retry on `400`, `401`, `403`, `404` errors.
  - Implement full exponential backoff with jitter.
  - Parse and respect the `Retry-After` header for rate-limit response `429`.

---

### Request Manager

#### [MODIFY] [RequestManager.ts](file:///m:/NEXORA%20GEN/AnimOrg2/backend/src/utils/RequestManager.ts)
- Verify pending requests are properly cleared.
- Ensure rejected promises are not reused or stored, preventing future requests from being poisoned.

---

### Services & Controllers

#### [MODIFY] [HomeService.ts](file:///m:/NEXORA%20GEN/AnimOrg2/backend/src/services/HomeService.ts)
- Replace `Promise.all` with `Promise.allSettled`.
- Return remaining successful datasets if any upstream requests fail (non-blocking).

---

### Cleanups

#### [DELETE] Obsolete and duplicated code
- Scan the directory and cleanup any dead/obsolete files (such as `jikanService.ts` if it exists).

## Verification Plan

### Automated / Diagnostic Script
We will write a temporary diagnostic script `verify_endpoints.ts` (stored in `/tmp/` to keep the workspace clean) that will make requests to our running local backend on `http://localhost:5000` to verify:
1. `GET /api/anime/21` (Anime details)
2. `GET /api/anime/search?q=naruto` (Search)
3. `GET /api/home` (Home aggregator)
4. Other endpoints: Top, Season, Upcoming, Schedule, Characters, Recommendations, Episodes.

### Manual Verification
1. Run the server using `npm run dev`.
2. Inspect log outputs to ensure retries, retry delay times, and cache hit/miss statuses are logged cleanly and not spammed.
3. Validate compilation of TypeScript via `npm run build`.
